A lawsuit by the estate of Adrian Jacobs against Scholastic, claiming that J. K. Rowling's Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire plagiarised one of his own works, is dismissed by a court in the United States. (BBC)51-year-old Texan Cornelius Dupree, freed on parole in July 2010 after serving 30 of a 75 year sentence for aggravated robbery, has his conviction quashed after he was found to be innocent of the crime through DNA evidence. (BBC)